</a></p>

<h2><a id=3D"needs" name=3D"needs"></a>Who needs an EIN</h2>

<p>You need an EIN if you:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Have employees</li>
	<li>Will need to pay employment, excise or alcohol, tobacco, and firearms =
taxes</li>
	<li>Withhold taxes on income, other than wages, paid to a non-resident ali=
en</li>
</ul>

<p>If you don=E2=80=99t need an EIN for federal tax purposes, you can still=
 request one for banking or state tax purposes. EINs are not intended for o=
ther activities, such as state tax lien auctions, sales or lotteries.</p>

<p>You also need an EIN to operate any of these entities:</p>

<ul>
	<li><a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" da=
ta-entity-uuid=3D"1cb7c84e-bb97-4410-847f-3281d4bc569a" href=3D"https://www=
.irs.gov/businesses/partnerships" title=3D"Partnerships">Partnership</a></l=
i>
	<li><a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" da=
ta-entity-uuid=3D"dd95fc99-55cd-4591-b530-b1778e82688a" href=3D"https://www=
.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/limited-liability-compan=
y-llc" title=3D"Limited liability company (LLC)">Limited liability company =
(LLC)</a></li>
	<li><a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" da=
ta-entity-uuid=3D"98867ad7-aedd-4449-930a-f5e430e90257" href=3D"https://www=
.irs.gov/corporations" title=3D"Corporations">Corporation</a></li>
	<li><a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" da=
ta-entity-uuid=3D"1db2952e-bec4-4725-9662-1f4e11dc7c38" href=3D"https://www=
.irs.gov/charities-and-nonprofits" title=3D"Charities and nonprofits">Tax-e=
xempt organization</a></li>
	<li><a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" da=
ta-entity-uuid=3D"84aa595c-528a-40b0-a985-569b0adfb16f" href=3D"https://www=
.irs.gov/individuals/file-an-estate-tax-income-tax-return" title=3D"File an=
 estate tax income tax return">Estate</a></li>
	<li><a data-entity-substitution=3D"pup_linkit_media" data-entity-type=3D"m=
edia" data-entity-uuid=3D"7422cf24-24cc-4087-8c48-53ba19c87e2d" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/p1635.pdf" title=3D"0214 Publ 1635            =
               (PDF)">Trust <span class=3D"link-label label-file label-file=
-pdf">PDF</span></a> (except certain grantor-owned revocable trusts)</li>
	<li><a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" da=
ta-entity-uuid=3D"2eebc1a8-523e-42a2-b218-97cdcb15454f" href=3D"https://www=
.irs.gov/retirement-plans/plan-sponsor/types-of-retirement-plans" title=3D"=
Types of retirement plans">Retirement plan or individual retirement account=
 (IRA)</a></li>
	<li><a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" da=
ta-entity-uuid=3D"6a96d504-11bd-489e-a29e-63ee48d41d54" href=3D"https://www=
.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-publication-938" title=3D"About Publication 938, =
Real Estate Mortgage Investment Conduits (REMICs) Reporting Information (An=
d Other Collateralized Debt Obligations (CDOs))">Real estate mortgage inves=
tment conduit</a></li>
	<li><a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" da=
ta-entity-uuid=3D"6e528b15-76e8-4baf-874f-0e0133f7fada" href=3D"https://www=
.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-publication-225" title=3D"About Publication 225, =
Farmer's Tax Guide">Farmers' cooperative</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Find more in <a data-entity-substitution=3D"pup_linkit_media" data-entit=
y-type=3D"media" data-entity-uuid=3D"7422cf24-24cc-4087-8c48-53ba19c87e2d" =
href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/p1635.pdf" title=3D"0214 Publ 1635 =
                          (PDF)">Understanding Your EIN, Publication 1635 <=
span class=3D"link-label label-file label-file-pdf">PDF</span></a>.</p>

<h2><a id=3D"before" name=3D"before"></a>Before you apply</h2>

<p><strong>Form your entity first:&nbsp;</strong>If you=E2=80=99re creating=
 a <a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" data=
-entity-uuid=3D"aa4be211-2ae1-440e-86ad-d53418a58a7f" href=3D"https://www.i=
rs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/business-structures" title=
=3D"Business structures">legal entity</a> (LLC, partnership, corporation), =
register it with your state before you apply for an EIN. This includes tax =
exempt organizations.</p>

<p><strong>Tax exempt organizations:</strong> Don't apply for an EIN until =
your organization is legally formed. Most organizations (<a href=3D"https:/=
/prod.edit.irs.gov/charities-non-profits/annual-exempt-organization-return-=
who-must-file">see exceptions</a>) are subject to automatic revocation of t=
heir tax-exempt status if <a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-en=
tity-type=3D"node" data-entity-uuid=3D"fccbd456-f25a-4765-bb7a-d6fdac58b9b7=
" href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/charities-non-profits/annual-filing-and-forms=
" title=3D"Annual filing and forms">required returns or notices aren't file=
d for 3 consecutive years</a>.</p>

<p><b>Political organizations: </b>You must have an EIN to file&nbsp;<a dat=
a-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" data-entity-u=
uid=3D"71157174-4f5f-4c33-bc0c-e94976d91e8a" href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/fo=
rms-pubs/about-form-8871" title=3D"About Form 8871, Political Organization =
Notice of Section 527 Status">Form 8871, Political Organization Notice of S=
ection 527 Status</a>. File this form within 24 hours of creating your orga=
nization to become tax exempt.</p>

<h3>Business Name &amp; Address Rules</h3>

<p>IRS systems allow only letters (A-Z), numbers (0-9), hyphens (-), and am=
persands (&amp;) in business names. If your legal name contains:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Symbols (+, @, .) =E2=86=92 Spell them out or remove them with a space=
 (Jones.Com =E2=86=92 Jones Dot Com or Jones Com).</li>
	<li>Slashes (\ /) =E2=86=92 Use a hyphen instead.</li>
	<li>Apostrophes (=E2=80=99) =E2=86=92 Remove them without adding a space.<=
/li>
</ul>

<p>The IRS allows only 35 characters for street addresses. Enter key detail=
s (like apartment or suite numbers). Your address will be checked with USPS=
, and you=E2=80=99ll have a chance to fix it if needed.</p>

<h2><a id=3D"ways" name=3D"ways"></a>Ways to apply for an EIN</h2>

<p>If your principal place of business is in the U.S., you can get an EIN i=
n these ways:</p>

<ul>
	<li><a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" da=
ta-entity-uuid=3D"fb30561d-0006-42ad-8821-bfe002d28c63" href=3D"https://www=
.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/get-an-employer-identifi=
cation-number" title=3D"Get an employer identification number">Apply online=
</a>. Get an EIN now, free, direct from the IRS.</li>
	<li>Fax <a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node=
" data-entity-uuid=3D"fb92f365-744a-439a-81e4-ac467f7172b0" href=3D"https:/=
/www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-ss-4" title=3D"About Form SS-4, Applicat=
ion for Employer Identification Number (EIN)">Form SS-4, Application for Em=
ployer Identification Number</a> to <a href=3D"tel:855-641-6935">855-641-69=
35</a>. If you apply by fax and provide a fax number, IRS will fax a cover =
sheet with the EIN back to you in 4 business days. We no longer provide the=
 Form SS-4 notated with the EIN.</li>
	<li>Mail Form SS-4 to Internal Revenue Service, Attn: EIN Operation, Cinci=
nnati, OH 45999. You=E2=80=99ll get your EIN in about 4 weeks.</li>
</ul>

<h3><a id=3D"international" name=3D"international"></a>International EIN ap=
plicants</h3>

<p>If your principal place of business is outside the U.S., you can apply f=
or an EIN by phone at <a href=3D"tel:267-941-1099">267-941-1099</a> Monday =
=E2=80=93 Friday, 6 a.m. to 11 p.m. Eastern time or submit <a data-entity-s=
ubstitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" data-entity-uuid=3D"fb9=
2f365-744a-439a-81e4-ac467f7172b0" href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/a=
bout-form-ss-4" title=3D"About Form SS-4, Application for Employer Identifi=
cation Number (EIN)">Form SS-4</a>: by:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Fax 855-215-1627 (within the U.S.) or 304-707-9471 (outside the U.S.).=
</li>
	<li>Mail to Internal Revenue Service, Attn: EIN International Operation, C=
incinnati, OH 45999.</li>
</ul>

<p>You can apply only for <strong>1 EIN per day</strong>, whether online or=
 by phone, mail or fax.</p>

<h2><a id=3D"whois" name=3D"whois"></a>Who is a responsible party</h2>

<p>On the EIN application, you must name the person in charge of the entity=
 and its assets, called the <a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-=
entity-type=3D"node" data-entity-uuid=3D"742f8884-b369-4301-a966-3610abecd3=
7b" href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/r=
esponsible-parties-and-nominees" title=3D" Responsible parties and nominees=
">responsible party</a>. The application must generally include the respons=
ible party=E2=80=99s:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Name</li>
	<li>Social Security, individual taxpayer ID, or employer identification nu=
mber (for entities)</li>
	<li>Signature</li>
</ul>

<p><strong><a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"no=
de" data-entity-uuid=3D"742f8884-b369-4301-a966-3610abecd37b" href=3D"https=
://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/responsible-partie=
s-and-nominees" title=3D" Responsible parties and nominees">Nominees</a> ar=
e not authorized to apply for an EIN</strong>. A nominee who applies for an=
 EIN puts the entity=E2=80=99s information and privacy at risk.</p>

<h2><a id=3D"report" name=3D"report"></a>Report beneficial owners to FinCEN=
 when required</h2>

<p>Some corporations, limited liability companies, and other entities may b=
e required to report information on beneficial owners (the people who ultim=
ately own or control the company) to the U.S. Department of the Treasury's =
Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN). Find out if you must <a data=
-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" data-entity-uu=
id=3D"a5f0a557-6e5c-4791-8ba7-d838b6bdc4e2" href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/bus=
inesses/report-beneficial-owner-information" title=3D"Report beneficial own=
er information">report beneficial owners</a>.</p>

<p><a data-entity-substitution=3D"pup_linkit_media" data-entity-type=3D"med=
ia" data-entity-uuid=3D"323d258c-ca5b-444b-804e-33f3bdf1d9f4" href=3D"https=
://fincen.gov/boi" title=3D"Beneficial Ownership Information Reporting | Fi=
nCEN.gov" class=3D"ext" data-extlink=3D"">Beneficial Ownership Information =
Reporting<span class=3D"fa-ext extlink" aria-label=3D"(link is external)" r=
ole=3D"img" aria-hidden=3D"false"><span class=3D"fa fa-external-link fa-ext=
ernal-link-alt" data-extlink-placement=3D"append"></span></span></a></p>

<h2><a id=3D"use" name=3D"use"></a>When you can use your EIN</h2>

<p>You can use your EIN immediately for most business needs. For example, w=
hen you:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Open a bank account</li>
	<li>Apply for business licenses</li>
	<li>File a tax return by mail</li>
</ul>

<p>Wait up to 2 weeks to:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Pass an IRS Taxpayer ID Number (TIN) Matching Program</li>
	<li>E-file a tax return</li>
	<li>Make tax deposits and pay electronically =E2=80=93 See <a data-entity-=
substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" data-entity-uuid=3D"95=
ed5034-9c8e-47ba-a222-e7deccbff110" href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/publication=
s/p15" title=3D"Publication 15 (2025), (Circular E), Employer's Tax Guide">=
Circular E, Employer=E2=80=99s Tax Guide, Publication 15, when you receive =
your EIN</a> and <a data-entity-substitution=3D"pup_linkit_media" data-enti=
ty-type=3D"media" data-entity-uuid=3D"a5673c2f-4672-457a-8f07-106f01db3d1a"=
 href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/p4275.pdf" title=3D"1007 Publ 4275=
                           (PDF)">EFTPS Express Enrollment for New Business=
es, Publication 4275 <span class=3D"link-label label-file label-file-pdf">P=
DF</span></a></li>
</ul>

<h2><a id=3D"waiting" name=3D"waiting"></a>If you=E2=80=99re waiting for an=
 EIN</h2>

<p>If your tax return is due and you haven=E2=80=99t received your EIN, wri=
te =E2=80=9CApplied For=E2=80=9D and the date that you applied for it in th=
e space shown for the number.</p>

<p>If you don't have your EIN by the time a deposit is due send your paymen=
t to the <a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node=
" data-entity-uuid=3D"187b5f14-fd90-42f9-b608-12891e80bb5a" href=3D"https:/=
/www.irs.gov/filing/where-to-file-tax-returns-addresses-listed-by-return-ty=
pe" title=3D"Where to file tax returns - addresses listed by return type">s=
ervice center address</a> for your state. Make your check or money order pa=
yable to Internal Revenue Service and show your name (as shown on the SS-4)=
, address, kind of tax, period covered, and the date you applied for your E=
IN.</p>

<h2><a id=3D"get" name=3D"get"></a>When to get a new EIN</h2>

<p>You need a new EIN, in general, when you change your entity=E2=80=99s ow=
nership or structure.</p>

<p>You don=E2=80=99t need a new EIN to <a data-entity-substitution=3D"canon=
ical" data-entity-type=3D"node" data-entity-uuid=3D"35b1fce5-4595-4cc2-a814=
-5d42f7e84fbd" href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/businesses/business-name-change"=
 title=3D"Business name change">change your business name</a>, address or r=
esponsible party.</p>

<p>Find more on <a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=
=3D"node" data-entity-uuid=3D"fa80c904-501c-4596-8d38-867bb6934d89" href=3D=
"https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/when-to-get-=
a-new-ein" title=3D"When to get a new EIN">when to get a new EIN</a>.</p>

<h2 id=3D"whennolongerneed"><a id=3D"nolonger" name=3D"nolonger"></a>When y=
ou no longer need an EIN</h2>

<p>If you no longer need your EIN, we can=E2=80=99t cancel it, but we can <=
a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"node" data-ent=
ity-uuid=3D"100de054-2d19-486b-a21b-80ff9e3f813d" href=3D"https://www.irs.g=
ov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/if-you-no-longer-need-your-ein=
" title=3D"If you no longer need your EIN">deactivate it</a>.</p>

<div class=3D"accordion-list" data-fix-id=3D"accordion1730847777476_715104"=
>
<div class=3D"table-responsive">
<div aria-multiselectable=3D"true" class=3D"panel-group accordion-list-grou=
p accordion-list-items" id=3D"accordion1730847777476_715104" role=3D"tablis=
t">
<div class=3D"collapsible-item panel panel-default" data-fix-id=3D"Collapsi=
