<h4 class=3D"collapsible-item-title panel-title" id=3D"multipleein"><a aria=
-controls=3D"collapseCollapsible1747238390990" aria-expanded=3D"false" clas=
s=3D"collapsed collapsible-item-title-link pup-accordion-chevron-rt" data-t=
oggle=3D"collapse" href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/businesses/employer-identifi=
cation-number#collapseCollapsible1747238390990" role=3D"button" data-once=
=3D"links-once"><span>&nbsp;</span>Multiple EINs or entities<span>&nbsp;</s=
pan></a></h4>
</div>

<div aria-labelledby=3D"accordion_header_help" class=3D"collapse collapsibl=
e-item-collapse panel-collapse" id=3D"collapseCollapsible1747238390990" rol=
e=3D"tabpanel">
<div class=3D"table-responsive">
<div class=3D"collapsible-item-body panel-body"><p class=3D"visually-hidden=
">&nbsp;</p>
<p><a id=3D"multiple" name=3D"multiple"></a>A business entity should have o=
nly one EIN.</p>

<p>If you have more than one EIN and aren=E2=80=99t sure which to use, call=
 the Business and Specialty Tax Line at <a href=3D"tel:800-829-4933">800-82=
9-4933</a> (TTY <a href=3D"tel:800-829-4059">800-829-4059</a>) and we=E2=80=
=99ll tell you which number to use.</p>

<p>If you took over another employer's business, use your own EIN to report=
 and deposit employment taxes. Don=E2=80=99t use the prior employer's EIN. =
Find more in <a data-entity-substitution=3D"canonical" data-entity-type=3D"=
node" data-entity-uuid=3D"95ed5034-9c8e-47ba-a222-e7deccbff110" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.irs.gov/publications/p15" title=3D"Publication 15 (2025), (Circula=
r E), Employer's Tax Guide">Circular E, Employer=E2=80=99s Tax Guide, Publi=
cation 15</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

